  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour your dried chickpeas into a large bowl, then cover them generously with water. Pop them in the fridge and leave them to soak overnight."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely slice one of your red onions and your radishes."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your onions and radishes to a bowl along with the juice of 1 of your lemons and a good pinch of salt. Scrunch up with your hands to lightly pickle, then set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your tahini to a bowl along with your vegan mayo and the juice of 1 lemon. Pour in 2 tbsp water, then whisk until you have a smooth sauce - it will look lumpy at first, but then get smooth. Add more water if necessary to get a thick, glossy consistency. Season to taste with salt."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop your remaining red onion, cloves of garlic, parsley and coriander - stalks and all."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dry your chickpeas with a tea towel, then add them to the barrel of a food processor with your red onion, garlic, parsley, coriander, dried cumin, dried coriander, aleppo chilli, gram flour, baking powder, and a level tsp of salt. Whizz to combine to a smooth paste - the smoother it is, the easier your falafel will be to shape."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Take a baseball-sized handful of the mixture, and gently shape it into a patty. Repeat 3 more times."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a generous glug of vegetable oil in a frying pan. Add your falafel patties, and fry for 4 mins on each side until deeply golden brown and crispy."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Halve your burger buns and toast them in a dry frying pan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice your cucumber."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Spread your tahini mayo on your burger bases, then add a dollop of chilli jam. Add a falafel burger, your sliced cucumber and pickles on top. Add a little more tahini mayo to the top of the bun, then place this on top."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
